# Cursor Rules for Portfolio Project

# Project Structure
/portfolio/
  /static/
    /css/
      styles.css
    /js/
      main.js
    /images/
  /templates/
    layout.html
    index.html
    about.html
    projects.html
    contact.html
  /instance/
  app.py
  requirements.txt
  .env
  README.md

# File Patterns
*.py = Python files (Flask backend)
*.html = HTML template files
*.js = JavaScript files
*.css = CSS files using Tailwind

# Coding Standards
- Use 4 spaces for indentation in Python files
- Use 2 spaces for indentation in HTML/CSS/JS files
- Follow PEP 8 style guide for Python code
- Use meaningful variable and function names
- Add comments for complex logic
- Keep functions small and focused

# Flask Guidelines
- Use Blueprint for route organization
- Implement proper error handling
- Use environment variables for sensitive data
- Follow RESTful principles for APIs
- Use Flask-SQLAlchemy for database operations
- Use Flask-Mail for email functionality
- Use Jinja2 for templating

# Frontend Guidelines
- Use Tailwind CSS for styling
- Make responsive design a priority
- Implement progressive enhancement
- Optimize images and assets
- Ensure accessibility standards
- Use semantic HTML elements

# Security Rules
- Implement CSRF protection
- Sanitize user inputs
- Use secure headers
- Keep dependencies updated
- Follow OWASP security guidelines

# Performance Guidelines
- Minimize HTTP requests
- Optimize database queries
- Use caching where appropriate
- Compress static assets
- Lazy load images
